01:02:16,199 --> 01:02:18,479
Mr. Kusakabe. Telegram

478
01:02:20,303 --> 01:02:22,263
Mr. Kusakabe

479
01:02:22,672 --> 01:02:24,042
Telegram

480
01:02:26,409 --> 01:02:27,579
Anyone home?

481
01:02:34,584 --> 01:02:36,254
Nanny

482
01:02:40,991 --> 01:02:42,361
I'm here

483
01:02:44,294 --> 01:02:45,933
This one is ripe

484
01:02:55,572 --> 01:02:56,862
What about this one?

485
01:02:57,173 --> 01:02:58,283
That's good, too

486
01:03:04,914 --> 01:03:07,464
Your garden's a treasure house

487
01:03:08,752 --> 01:03:10,922
Let's take a little break

488
01:03:17,193 --> 01:03:19,773
These should be cold now

489
01:03:20,263 --> 01:03:21,633
Looks delicious

490
01:03:31,474 --> 01:03:32,584
So good

491
01:03:32,876 --> 01:03:36,416
The sun blessed these

492
01:03:37,047 --> 01:03:38,717
So they're
really good for you

493
01:03:39,082 --> 01:03:40,692
Would they help my Mom, too?

494
01:03:41,051 --> 01:03:42,221
Of course

495
01:03:42,519 --> 01:03:45,769
If she eats my vegetables
she'll get better right away

496
01:03:46,356 --> 01:03:48,696
She's supposed to
be back next Saturday

497
01:03:49,159 --> 01:03:51,439
She'll sleep in my bed

498
01:03:51,895 --> 01:03:52,825
At last

499
01:03:53,096 --> 01:03:55,346
That's wonderful

500
01:03:55,799 --> 01:03:57,379
But it's only
for a couple of days

501
01:03:57,734 --> 01:03:59,464
To get used to the new house

502
01:03:59,836 --> 01:04:02,705
I see

503
01:04:03,239 --> 01:04:05,459
We'll feed her
lots of vegetables, then

504
01:04:05,909 --> 01:04:09,009
I'll give her this corn
I picked

505
01:04:09,579 --> 01:04:11,509
I'm sure
she'll be very pleased

506
01:04:11,915 --> 01:04:13,115
iknow

507
01:04:20,990 --> 01:04:22,919
